A Krull domain $A$ is integrally closed because it is the intersection of its localizations $A_{\mathfrak{p}}$ at height one primes $\mathfrak{p}$, and each $A_{\mathfrak{p}}$ is a discrete valuation ring (DVR). Since DVRs are integrally closed and the integral closure of $A$ in its fraction field is contained in the integral closure of each $A_{\mathfrak{p}}$, the result follows.

